SIMPLE: relate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relate
<hw>Re*late"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Related</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Relating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>relater</ets> to recount, LL. <ets>relatare</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>relatus</ets>, used as p. p. of <ets>referre</ets>. See
<er>Elate</er>, and cf. <er>Refer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bring
back; to restore.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> Abate your zealous haste, till morrow next again⟦br⟧
Both light of heaven and strength of men <qex>relate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To refer; to ascribe, as to a source.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To recount; to narrate; to tell over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This heavy act with heavy heart <qex>relate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To ally by connection or kindred.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To relate one's self</b></col>, <cd>to vent thoughts in
words.</cd> <mark>[R.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To tell; recite; narrate; recount; rehearse;
report; detail; describe.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Relate
<hw>Re*late"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To stand in some
relation; to have bearing or concern; to pertain; to refer; -- with
<xex>to</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All negative or privative words <qex>relate</qex> positive
ideas.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make reference; to take account.</def> <mark>[R.
& Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Reckoning by the years of their own consecration without
<qex>relating</qex> to any imperial account.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Related</ent>⟦br⟧
